<!-- Key Factors -->
<section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-xl">What to Look for in a Financial Advisor</h2>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-2">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="service-tag">Factor 1</div>
                <h3>Fiduciary Standard</h3>
                <p>A fiduciary advisor is legally obligated to act in your best interest. This is the highest standard of care in financial advice. Not all advisors are fiduciaries — many operate under a lesser "suitability" standard.</p>

                <div class="mt-md">
                    <h4 class="text-accent">Questions to Ask:</h4>
                    <ul style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-left: 1.5rem;">
                        <li>Are you a fiduciary at all times?</li>
                        <li>Will you put that in writing?</li>
                        <li>Do you receive commissions from any products?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <div class="service-tag">Factor 2</div>
                <h3>Specialization</h3>
                <p>Financial planning is broad. The best advisor for your retirement is one who specializes in retirement income planning, not a generalist who handles everything from college savings to business insurance.</p>

                <div class="mt-md">
                    <h4 class="text-accent">Questions to Ask:</h4>
                    <ul style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-left: 1.5rem;">
                        <li>What percentage of your clients are retirees?</li>
                        <li>Do you specialize in retirement income planning?</li>
                        <li>What tax planning strategies do you use?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <div class="service-tag">Factor 3</div>
                <h3>Fee Structure</h3>
                <p>Understand how your advisor gets paid. Fee-only advisors charge clients directly and don't earn commissions. Fee-based advisors may charge fees AND earn commissions, creating potential conflicts.</p>

                <div class="mt-md">
                    <h4 class="text-accent">Questions to Ask:</h4>
                    <ul style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-left: 1.5rem;">
                        <li>Are you fee-only or fee-based?</li>
                        <li>What is your total cost to me annually?</li>
                        <li>Are there any hidden or additional fees?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <div class="service-tag">Factor 4</div>
                <h3>Experience & Track Record</h3>
                <p>Look for advisors with significant experience, particularly with clients in your financial situation. Years in business, client retention, and community involvement all matter.</p>

                <div class="mt-md">
                    <h4 class="text-accent">Questions to Ask:</h4>
                    <ul style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-left: 1.5rem;">
                        <li>How long have you been advising clients?</li>
                        <li>What's your client retention rate?</li>
                        <li>Can you describe your planning process?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Utah-Specific Considerations -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-xl">Utah-Specific Retirement Planning Considerations</h2>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-3">
            <div class="card">
                <h3 class="text-accent">Utah Tax Landscape</h3>
                <p>Utah has a flat 4.55% state income tax. Understanding how this interacts with federal tax planning is essential for Utah retirees. The state retirement credit can also reduce your tax burden.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h3 class="text-accent">Cost of Living</h3>
                <p>Utah County's cost of living has risen significantly. Your retirement plan needs to account for local housing costs, healthcare expenses, and inflation specific to the Wasatch Front.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h3 class="text-accent">Local Expertise</h3>
                <p>An advisor familiar with Utah's regulatory environment, local tax laws, and community resources provides added value over a remote advisor unfamiliar with the area.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Red Flags -->
<section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-xl">Red Flags to Watch For</h2>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-2">
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Warning Signs</h3>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-left: 1.5rem;">
                    <li>Guaranteeing specific investment returns</li>
                    <li>Pressuring you to make quick decisions</li>
                    <li>Refusing to disclose their fee structure</li>
                    <li>Recommending products from their own company</li>
                    <li>Not asking detailed questions about your situation</li>
                    <li>Offering a one-size-fits-all plan</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h3>Green Flags</h3>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-left: 1.5rem;">
                    <li>Fiduciary commitment in writing</li>
                    <li>Transparent, understandable fee structure</li>
                    <li>Thorough discovery process before recommendations</li>
                    <li>Specialization in your specific needs</li>
                    <li>Strong community reputation and involvement</li>
                    <li>Regular reviews and proactive communication</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

